Package com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support

Class WrapperRandom

java.lang.Object
java.util.Random
com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.WrapperRandom
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class WrapperRandom extends Random
If, for whatever reason, you need a Random and all you have is an EnhancedRandom from this library, you can give that EnhancedRandom to WrapperRandom(EnhancedRandom) and then use this as a replacement for java.util.Random.

      public WrapperRandom​(@Nonnull EnhancedRandom rng)

    • WrapperRandom

      public WrapperRandom​(@Nonnull EnhancedRandom rng, long seed)
      Uses the given EnhancedRandom for all operations it can (everything but Streams), and seeds both that EnhancedRandom and the inherited Random state with the given seed.
      Parameters:
      rng - an EnhancedRandom that will be referenced directly (not copied) and will be seeded with seed
      seed - a long seed (which can be any long) that will be used with EnhancedRandom.setSeed(long)

    • WrapperRandom

      Creates a WrapperRandom around a FourWheelRandom, seeded with the given seed.
